 Neque enim aquarum illuvionibus text reads aquarumi lluvionibus tibi, Sename, sapientissimus text reads Tibi +peri daimoniou tou Sokratous+ so in original: should be +Sôkratous+ [1.] Alibi: maligni. [2.] Deest in aliis codicibus. text reads aliiis [4.] Alibi: exsilisse. text reads exsiliise

 Liber Quartus

 cur potanae, voluptiae[2], libertinae[3] text reads volupiae ante legis promulgationem text reads promu gationem usque ad Abrahami aetatem text reads Ahrahami Vox enim hebraea #letanot# text reads #letavot# ex abditis Hebraeorum arcanis promisit text reads promsit dilatio vitae periculum sit allatura text reads allutara alii ab hebraica voce #t/f/l/h# text reads #t/f/l/ch/n# O hominum, pecudum, divûmque so in original: possible mistranscription of div[~u] mentis ad omnia concitas text reads coecitas

 Liber Quintus

 quisquam vestrûm non falleretur so in original: possible mistranscription of vestr[~u] Sed ut proverbio dicitur: +Rhaon esti mômeisthai ê mimeisthai+ text reads +mimeisthei+ ipsa mentis actio sit contemplatio text reads comtemplatio Vocem enim #shevet# sceptrum text reads #shevem# quasi diceret #beno# text reads #bano# scilicet #betula# vel #na'ara# text reads #betula# (twice) Tametsi dictum illud Davidis text reads Tamesti oratio Christi est ad Pharisaeos. Ut illis eriperet text reads ad Pharisaeos. ut Tametsi plerisque placet text reads Tamesti uxorem propinqui viduam text reads pronpinqui Josephum et Mariam a Galilaea text reads Galialea [1.] Alius: Theophilus. (Theophylactus in cap. 1. Luc. Cypriani serm. de laps.) closing ")" missing

 Liber Sextus

 quodammodo manuduci rectissime judicarunt so in original: "manu duci"? Josephum, Matthiae filium text reads Mathatiae sacratissimum numen #YHWH# so in original: "nomen"? [1.] ... Jerem. 43. 45. 47. 31. 32. order as in original Qui peccaverit in me, inquit,[3] comma missing in original voce chaldaea #ravod# so in original: #kavod#? +pan gar to ou prôton ouch haploun+ text reads +... ouk+ humanam carnem assumserit text reads asssumserit qui coecutiunt ad indigentium inopiam spelling as in original: normal form is "caecutiunt" [3.] Ptolem ni. centiloquo. so in original aut publice fornicari text reads formicari quique sunt ingenio hebetiores text reads hebetiore canerent suam[1] #hashuva# (accubationem) text reads #hashvuva# on both occurrences viginti circiter hominum millia necarentur.[1] Sed text reads necarentur,[1] Sed Ad pag. 295 lin. 10 pertinet subsequens carmen graecum See footnote beginning "Graeca verba in omnibus...."

